'''''Magnum opus''''' (sometimes ''Opus magnum''), from the [[Latin]] meaning ''great work'', refers to the best or most renowned achievement of an [[author]], [[artist]], or [[composer]]. It can also refer to an individual literary or artistic masterpiece.

==A List of Albums Generally Considered to be a Band's Magnum Opus==
*''[[Dark Side of the Moon]]'' by [[Pink Floyd]]
*''[[In the Court of the Crimson King]]'' by [[King Crimson]]
*''[[The Divine Wings of Tragedy]]'' by [[Symphony X]]
*''[[Dirt (album)|Dirt]]'' by [[Alice in Chains]]
*''[[Nevermind (album)|Nevermind]]'' by [[Nirvana (band)|Nirvana]]
*''[[London Calling (album)|London Calling]]'' by [[The Clash]]
*''[[The Velvet Underground and Nico]]'' by [[the Velvet Underground]]
*''[[Images and Words]]'' by [[Dream Theater]]
*''[[All Eyez on Me]]'' by [[Tupac]]
*''[[Kind of Blue]]'' by [[Miles Davis]]

